This technology is not really new. The new generation Ka band spot-beam satellites
already on-station have capability to route within transponders on the same "spot".

HughesNet is rumored to be ready to provide service on SpaceWay that would allow a customer
to set up their own teleport at their own location and have their feeders route to it.

Other satellites, like TDRS have the ability to relay between themselves, but not
at the IP protocol level.

Maybe new for the military.

