The whole rationale of Internet routing is that a message passes by
the "lowest cost" route. Different messages may have different
priorites and may be encrypted.

If traffic is FORCED to go be a particular route the Pentagon will
wind up with a inferior service. If fiber optics can transmit at 40GHz
per fiber who needs space?

The Pentagon will have to get used to the idea that it no longer the
driving force in technology, It would do far better to investigate
COTS type solutions.

